---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import ProjectHero from '../../../../components/ProjectHero.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const IMG = (p: string) => `/images/wp/${p}`;

const trail = [
  { slug: 'mystery', title: 'THE MYSTERY ENTERTAINMENT', path: `${base}en/mystery/` },
  { slug: 'hieke', title: 'THE HEIKE STORY', path: `${base}en/mystery/hieke/` },
];
---

<Layout title="The Heike Story — Japonéson" lang="en">
  <Header lang="en" />
  <main>
    <ProjectHero
      title="The Heike Story"
      subtitle="The 12th Century"
      titleColor="#ffffff"
      titleSize="60px"
      image={`${base}images/mystery/hero_hieke.jpg`}
      align="center"
      height={760}
      fit="cover"
      overlayTop={0}
      overlayBottom={0}
    />

    <div class="container breadcrumb-wrap">
      <Breadcrumb trail={trail} lang="en" />
    </div>

    <section class="intro">
      <div class="intro-inner">
        <p class="heike-quote">
          "The bell of Gion Shoja temple tolls, and its sound carries the truth: Nothing lasts forever."
        </p>

        <p class="heike-lead">
          This famous line begins "The Tale of the Heike," a story of power,
          loss, and the mystery of a clan that vanished into the sea at
          Shimonoseki.
        </p>

        <p>
          I have always felt a strange pull toward the Heike clan, even as a
          child. That's why I moved to Shimonoseki in spring 2022—to feel
          their story for myself. But in summer 2025, as I stood between the
          Akama Shrine and the Shunpanro, I noticed something dark.
          Something hidden. My journey to find the Heike began to reveal the
          deep shadows of the Meiji Restoration. It seems the mystery is much
          deeper than just a story of the past.
        </p>

        <hr class="red-divider" />

        <h2 class="overview">The Heike Story : A Story Overview</h2>

        <h3 class="num">1. What is "The Tale of the Heike"?</h3>
        <p>
          It is an epic account of the struggle between the Taira (Heike) and
          Minamoto (Genji) clans for control of Japan in the late 12th
          century. It is not just a record of war, but a masterpiece of
          literature that explores the themes of power, tragedy, and the
          fleeting nature of glory.
        </p>

        <h3 class="num">2. The Philosophy: "Mujo" (Impermanence)</h3>
        <p>
          The story begins with the famous line:
          <em>"The sound of the Gion Shoja bells echoes the impermanence of all things."</em>
          It emphasizes that nothing lasts forever—no matter how powerful a
          person or a clan becomes, they will eventually fall.
        </p>

        <h3 class="num">3. The Peak of Power: The Taira Clan</h3>
        <p>
          Under the leadership of Kiyomori Taira, the clan achieved
          unprecedented influence in the Imperial Court. In the famous
          literary work "The Tale of the Heike," they are depicted as an
          elite group with absolute authority.
        </p>

        <h3 class="num">4. The Turning Point: The Battle of Dan-no-ura (1185)</h3>
        <p>
          The final, decisive battle took place in <strong>Shimonoseki</strong>.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>A Sea of Crimson:</strong> The Heike, once masters of the sea, were cornered by the Minamoto fleet in the Shimonoseki Straits.</li>
          <li><strong>The Final Sacrifice:</strong> Realizing defeat was inevitable, the widow of Kiyomori took the 8-year-old Emperor Antoku in her arms and leaped into the ocean, saying, <em>"There is a capital city even beneath the waves."</em></li>
          <li><strong>The End of an Era:</strong> This tragic event marked the total destruction of the Heike clan and the beginning of the Shogunate (Samurai) era in Japan.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="num">5. Legacy and Rituals</h3>
        <p>The souls of the Heike are said to remain in the waters of Shimonoseki.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Akama Shrine:</strong> Formerly a Buddhist temple (Amida-ji), it was built to pacify the spirits of the drowned Heike and Emperor Antoku.</li>
          <li><strong>Hoichi the Earless:</strong> A famous ghost story set at this shrine, depicting a blind monk who played the biwa (lute) for the ghosts of the fallen samurai.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="red-section-start" />

    <section class="anime-block">
      <div class="anime-inner">
        <div class="anime-video">
          <iframe
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZW40VnNrowY"
            title="The Heike Story (Anime) PV"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        </div>
        <div class="anime-text">
          <h3 class="anime-title">Recommended: "The Heike Story" (Anime)</h3>
          <p>
            If you want to feel the emotional depth and the "Mujo"
            (impermanence) of this story visually, I highly recommend this
            anime. It beautifully depicts the bonds of the Taira clan and the
            tragic beauty of their fall. It's a perfect way to understand the
            summary of the events before you dive deeper into the mysteries of
            Shimonoseki.
          </p>
          <p>
            For those outside of Japan, you can find the anime "The Tale of
            the Heike" on Amazon Prime Video (it may require a rental or
            purchase depending on your region).
          </p>
          <p>
            If you want to understand the summary and feel the emotional
            atmosphere of the clan before exploring the mysteries I found in
            Shimonoseki, this beautifully crafted series is the best place to
            start.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="red-section-end" />
  </main>
  <Footer lang="en" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .breadcrumb-wrap { padding-top: 1rem; padding-bottom: 0; }

  .intro {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 3rem;
  }
  .intro-inner {
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .intro-inner p {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #2a2a2a;
    margin: 0 0 1.3rem;
  }
  .intro-inner strong { font-weight: 700; color: #1a1a1a; }
  .intro-inner em { font-style: italic; }

  .intro-inner p.heike-quote {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Infant', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 26px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .intro-inner p.heike-lead {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Infant', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: #2a2a2a;
    margin: 0 0 1.8rem;
  }

  .intro-inner hr.red-divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 6px solid var(--color-accent);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .intro-inner h2.overview {
    font-family: var(--font-display-cinzel);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 30px;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .intro-inner h3.num {
    font-family: 'Gabriela', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin: 2.2rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .intro-inner ul {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #2a2a2a;
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .intro-inner ul li { margin: 0 0 0.6rem; }

  .anime-block {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }
  .anime-inner {
    max-width: 1080px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 360px 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .anime-video {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    width: 100%;
    background: #000;
  }
  .anime-video iframe {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    border: 0;
  }
  .anime-text h3.anime-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display-cinzel);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
  }
  .anime-text p {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #2a2a2a;
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
  }

  hr.red-section-start,
  hr.red-section-end {
    border: none;
    border-top: 6px solid var(--color-accent);
    max-width: 1080px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  hr.red-section-start { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  hr.red-section-end { margin-top: 2rem; }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .anime-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
    .anime-video { max-width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
